<p>Our unique classes focus on using isometric movements to fatigue muscle groups where bodies tend to struggle most-arms, thighs, seat and abdominals. Stretching is the secret ingredient to achieving the long, lean look of a dancer, and is added throughout all classes. Continuously evolving movements keep classes challenging, fun, and fresh. Our certified instructors enhance your experience with their strong backgrounds in ballet, Pilates and Fitness.</p><p><strong>EXPERIENCE A CLASS</strong> Upon your arrival, sign up for drop-in classes with our online scheduler or by downloading the free Mindbody Connect app. <a href="https://clients.mindbodyonline.com/classic/ws?studioid=27108&amp;stype=-103&amp;sView=week" target="_blank">Click here</a> to reserve your spot. Plan to arrive 5 minutes before your first class. You will complete a simple form so that we may understand your body and lifestyle. All equipment and mats are provided at no cost.</p><p><strong>ATTIRE</strong> Wear something you can move in, sweat in and feel comfortable in. Ballet slippers are preferred in Barre and Ballet classes to assist in the ease of some of our movements. Leather Ballet slippers are available for purchase for $22 at the front desk, and we will be happy to assist you. You may bring your own bottled water or you may purchase it at the front desk.</p><p><strong>FOR THE KIDDOS</strong> Free childcare is offered to all customers with no reservation needed at all classes except 7:00pm and Sunday classes. Ages 4 weeks and up welcome. Anyone under the age of 18 not taking class must be in the playroom.</p><p><strong>BEGINNERS OR HAVE NOT WORKED OUT IN AWHILE</strong><span>&nbsp;We strive to make an atmosphere where everyone feels comfortable. Classes can be done by all shapes, sizes, and ages. No dancing experience is required since instructors provide modifications and easy-to-follow cues in all classes.</span></p><p><strong>WAIT LIST</strong> In the event that a class is full, our online